# --------------------------------------------------
# Adaptive Edge Weighting for Label Propagation
# Author: M. Karasuyama (karasuyama@nitech.ac.jp)
# --------------------------------------------------

This is a matlab implementation of adaptive edge weighting method for label propagation proposed by "Manifold-based similarity adaptation for label propagation" (NIPS 2013) and "Adaptive Edge Weighting for Graph-Based Learning Algorithms" (Machine Learning Journal 2017).

Main files:
[test_run1.m]: A test script for running the method using synthetic data shown in the above paper.
[AEW.m]: Optimizing edge weights for label propagation
[HGF.m]: Label propagation by the harmonic Gaussian field model

Python port:
- A paper-aligned Python port of AEW is available in the toolkit at
	`Thesis-Copilot-Toolkit/src/graph_construction/aew.py` and is used by the
	`build_graph(..., method='aew')` dispatcher (see `Thesis-Copilot-Toolkit/src/graph_construction/graph_constructors.py`).
	The port follows the MATLAB implementation and includes `generate_nngraph`
	heuristics and the AEW optimizer. Use the Python port for reproducible
	experiments and CI-friendly smoke tests.
